124MaybeHandle<Code> Factory::CodeBuilder::BuildInternal(
125 bool retry_allocation_or_fail) {
126 DirectHandle<TrustedByteArray> reloc_info =
127 NewTrustedByteArray(code_desc_.reloc_size);
128
129 // Basic block profiling data for builtins is stored in the JS heap rather
130 // than in separately-allocated C++ objects. Allocate that data now if
131 // appropriate.
132 DirectHandle<OnHeapBasicBlockProfilerData> on_heap_profiler_data;
133 if (V8_UNLIKELY(profiler_data_ && isolate_->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins())) {
134 on_heap_profiler_data = profiler_data_->CopyToJSHeap(isolate_);
135
136 // Add the on-heap data to a global list, which keeps it alive and allows
137 // iteration.
138 Handle<ArrayList> list(isolate_->heap()->basic_block_profiling_data(),
139 isolate_);
140 DirectHandle<ArrayList> new_list = ArrayList::Add(
141 isolate_, list, on_heap_profiler_data, AllocationType::kOld);
142 isolate_->heap()->SetBasicBlockProfilingData(new_list);
143 }
144
145 Tagged<HeapObject> istream_allocation =
146 AllocateUninitializedInstructionStream(retry_allocation_or_fail);
147 if (istream_allocation.is_null()) {
148 return {};
149 }
150
151 Handle<InstructionStream> istream;
152 {
153 // The InstructionStream object has not been fully initialized yet. We
154 // rely on the fact that no allocation will happen from this point on.
155 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
156 Tagged<InstructionStream> raw_istream = InstructionStream::Initialize(
157 istream_allocation,
158 ReadOnlyRoots(local_isolate_).instruction_stream_map(),
159 code_desc_.body_size(), code_desc_.constant_pool_offset, *reloc_info);
160 istream = handle(raw_istream, local_isolate_);
161 DCHECK(IsAligned(istream->instruction_start(), kCodeAlignment));
162 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!local_isolate_->heap()->heap()->code_region().is_empty(),
163 local_isolate_->heap()->heap()->code_region().contains(
164 istream->address()));
165 }
166
167 Handle<Code> code;
168 {
169 static_assert(InstructionStream::kOnHeapBodyIsContiguous);
170
171 NewCodeOptions new_code_options = {
172 kind_,
173 builtin_,
174 is_context_specialized_,
175 is_turbofanned_,
176 parameter_count_,
177 code_desc_.instruction_size(),
178 code_desc_.metadata_size(),
179 inlined_bytecode_size_,
180 osr_offset_,
181 code_desc_.handler_table_offset_relative(),
182 code_desc_.constant_pool_offset_relative(),
183 code_desc_.code_comments_offset_relative(),
184 code_desc_.builtin_jump_table_info_offset_relative(),
185 code_desc_.unwinding_info_offset_relative(),
186 interpreter_data_,
187 deoptimization_data_,
188 bytecode_offset_table_,
189 source_position_table_,
190 istream,
191 /*instruction_start=*/kNullAddress,
192 };
193 code = NewCode(new_code_options);
194 DCHECK_EQ(istream->body_size(), code->body_size());
195
196 {
197 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
198 Tagged<InstructionStream> raw_istream = *istream;
199
200 // Allow self references to created code object by patching the handle to
201 // point to the newly allocated InstructionStream object.
202 Handle<Object> self_reference;
203 if (self_reference_.ToHandle(&self_reference)) {
204 DCHECK_EQ(*self_reference,
205 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_).self_reference_marker());
206 DCHECK_NE(kind_, CodeKind::BASELINE);
207 if (isolate_->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins()) {
208 isolate_->builtins_constants_table_builder()->PatchSelfReference(
209 self_reference, istream);
210 }
211 self_reference.PatchValue(raw_istream);
212 }
213
214 // Likewise, any references to the basic block counters marker need to be
215 // updated to point to the newly-allocated counters array.
216 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!on_heap_profiler_data.is_null())) {
217 isolate_->builtins_constants_table_builder()
218 ->PatchBasicBlockCountersReference(
219 handle(on_heap_profiler_data->counts(), isolate_));
220 }
221
222 // Migrate generated code.
223 // The generated code can contain embedded objects (typically from
224 // handles) in a pointer-to-tagged-value format (i.e. with indirection
225 // like a handle) that are dereferenced during the copy to point
226 // directly to the actual heap objects. These pointers can include
227 // references to the code object itself, through the self_reference
228 // parameter.
229 istream->Finalize(*code, *reloc_info, code_desc_, isolate_->heap());
230
231#ifdef VERIFY_HEAP
232 if (v8_flags.verify_heap) {
233 HeapObject::VerifyCodePointer(isolate_, raw_istream);
234 }
235#endif
236 }
237 }
238
239 // TODO(leszeks): Remove stack_slots_, it's already in the instruction stream.
240 DCHECK_EQ(stack_slots_, code->stack_slots());
241
242#ifdef ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
243 if (V8_UNLIKELY(profiler_data_ && v8_flags.turbo_profiling_verbose)) {
244 std::ostringstream os;
245 code->Disassemble(nullptr, os, isolate_);
246 if (!on_heap_profiler_data.is_null()) {
247 DirectHandle<String> disassembly =
248 local_isolate_->factory()->NewStringFromAsciiChecked(
249 os.str().c_str(), AllocationType::kOld);
250 on_heap_profiler_data->set_code(*disassembly);
251 } else {
252 profiler_data_->SetCode(os);
253 }
254 }
255#endif // ENABLE_DISASSEMBLER
256
257 return code;
258}

260Tagged<HeapObject> Factory::CodeBuilder::AllocateUninitializedInstructionStream(
261 bool retry_allocation_or_fail) {
262 LocalHeap* heap = local_isolate_->heap();
263 Tagged<HeapObject> result;
264 const int object_size = InstructionStream::SizeFor(code_desc_.body_size());
265 if (retry_allocation_or_fail) {
266 // Only allowed to do `retry_allocation_or_fail` from the main thread.
267 // TODO(leszeks): Remove the retrying allocation, always use TryBuild in
268 // the code builder.
269 DCHECK(local_isolate_->is_main_thread());
270 result =
271 heap->heap()->allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
272 object_size, AllocationType::kCode, AllocationOrigin::kRuntime);
273 CHECK(!result.is_null());
274 return result;
275 } else {
276 // Return null if we cannot allocate the code object.
277 return heap->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kLightRetry>(
278 object_size, AllocationType::kCode);
279 }
280}

296Tagged<HeapObject> Factory::AllocateRawWithAllocationSite(
297 DirectHandle<Map> map, AllocationType allocation,
298 DirectHandle<AllocationSite> allocation_site) {
299 DCHECK(map->instance_type() != MAP_TYPE);
300 int size = map->instance_size();
301 if (!allocation_site.is_null()) {
302 DCHECK(V8_ALLOCATION_SITE_TRACKING_BOOL);
303 size += ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(AllocationMemento::kSize);
304 }
305 Tagged<HeapObject> result =
306 allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(size,
307 allocation);
308 WriteBarrierMode write_barrier_mode = allocation == AllocationType::kYoung
309 ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER
310 : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
311 result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map, write_barrier_mode);
312 if (!allocation_site.is_null()) {
313 int aligned_size = ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(map->instance_size());
314 Tagged<AllocationMemento> alloc_memento = UncheckedCast<AllocationMemento>(
315 Tagged<Object>(result.ptr() + aligned_size));
316 InitializeAllocationMemento(alloc_memento, *allocation_site);
317 }
318 return result;
319}
320
321void Factory::InitializeAllocationMemento(
322 Tagged<AllocationMemento> memento, Tagged<AllocationSite> allocation_site) {
323 DCHECK(V8_ALLOCATION_SITE_TRACKING_BOOL);
324 memento->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *allocation_memento_map(),
325 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
326 memento->set_allocation_site(allocation_site, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
327 if (v8_flags.allocation_site_pretenuring) {
328 allocation_site->IncrementMementoCreateCount();
329 }
330}

332Tagged<HeapObject> Factory::New(DirectHandle<Map> map,
333 AllocationType allocation) {
334 DCHECK(map->instance_type() != MAP_TYPE);
335 int size = map->instance_size();
336 Tagged<HeapObject> result =
337 allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(size,
338 allocation);
339 // New space objects are allocated white.
340 WriteBarrierMode write_barrier_mode = allocation == AllocationType::kYoung
341 ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER
342 : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
343 result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map, write_barrier_mode);
344 return result;
345}

407Handle<PropertyArray> Factory::NewPropertyArray(int length,
408 AllocationType allocation) {
409 DCHECK_LE(0, length);
410 if (length == 0) return empty_property_array();
411 Tagged<HeapObject> result = AllocateRawFixedArray(length, allocation);
412 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
413 result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *property_array_map(),
414 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
415 Tagged<PropertyArray> array = Cast<PropertyArray>(result);
416 array->initialize_length(length);
417 MemsetTagged(array->data_start(), read_only_roots().undefined_value(),
418 length);
419 return handle(array, isolate());
420}

422MaybeHandle<FixedArray> Factory::TryNewFixedArray(
423 int length, AllocationType allocation_type) {
424 DCHECK_LE(0, length);
425 if (length == 0) return empty_fixed_array();
426
427 int size = FixedArray::SizeFor(length);
428 Heap* heap = isolate()->heap();
429 AllocationResult allocation = heap->AllocateRaw(size, allocation_type);
430 Tagged<HeapObject> result;
431 if (!allocation.To(&result)) return MaybeHandle<FixedArray>();
432 if ((size > heap->MaxRegularHeapObjectSize(allocation_type)) &&
433 v8_flags.use_marking_progress_bar) {
434 LargePageMetadata::FromHeapObject(result)
435 ->marking_progress_tracker()
436 .Enable(size);
437 }
438 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
439 result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *fixed_array_map(),
440 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
441 Tagged<FixedArray> array = Cast<FixedArray>(result);
442 array->set_length(length);
443 MemsetTagged(array->RawFieldOfFirstElement(), *undefined_value(), length);
444 return handle(array, isolate());
445}

447Handle<FeedbackVector> Factory::NewFeedbackVector(
448 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared,
449 DirectHandle<ClosureFeedbackCellArray> closure_feedback_cell_array,
450 DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> parent_feedback_cell) {
451 int length = shared->feedback_metadata()->slot_count();
452 DCHECK_LE(0, length);
453 int size = FeedbackVector::SizeFor(length);
454
455 Tagged<FeedbackVector> vector =
456 Cast<FeedbackVector>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
457 size, AllocationType::kOld, *feedback_vector_map()));
458 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
459 vector->set_shared_function_info(*shared);
460 vector->set_length(length);
461 vector->set_invocation_count(0);
462 vector->set_invocation_count_before_stable(0);
463 vector->reset_osr_state();
464 vector->reset_flags();
465#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
466 vector->set_maybe_optimized_code(ClearedValue(isolate()));
467 vector->set_log_next_execution(v8_flags.log_function_events);
468#endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
469 vector->set_closure_feedback_cell_array(*closure_feedback_cell_array);
470 vector->set_parent_feedback_cell(*parent_feedback_cell);
471
472 // TODO(leszeks): Initialize based on the feedback metadata.
473 MemsetTagged(ObjectSlot(vector->slots_start()), *undefined_value(), length);
474 return handle(vector, isolate());
475}

504template <typename T>
505Handle<T> Factory::AllocateSmallOrderedHashTable(DirectHandle<Map> map,
506 int capacity,
507 AllocationType allocation) {
508 // Capacity must be a power of two, since we depend on being able
509 // to divide and multiple by 2 (kLoadFactor) to derive capacity
510 // from number of buckets. If we decide to change kLoadFactor
511 // to something other than 2, capacity should be stored as another
512 // field of this object.
513 DCHECK_EQ(T::kLoadFactor, 2);
514 capacity =
515 base::bits::RoundUpToPowerOfTwo32(std::max({T::kMinCapacity, capacity}));
516 capacity = std::min({capacity, T::kMaxCapacity});
517
518 DCHECK_LT(0, capacity);
519 DCHECK_EQ(0, capacity % T::kLoadFactor);
520
521 int size = T::SizeFor(capacity);
522 Tagged<HeapObject> result =
523 AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(size, allocation, *map);
524 Handle<T> table(Cast<T>(result), isolate());
525 table->Initialize(isolate(), capacity);
526 return table;
527}

578Handle<SwissNameDictionary> Factory::CreateCanonicalEmptySwissNameDictionary() {
579 // This function is only supposed to be used to create the canonical empty
580 // version and should not be used afterwards.
581 DCHECK(!ReadOnlyRoots(isolate()).is_initialized(
582 RootIndex::kEmptySwissPropertyDictionary));
583
584 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
585
586 DirectHandle<ByteArray> empty_meta_table =
587 NewByteArray(SwissNameDictionary::kMetaTableEnumerationDataStartIndex,
588 AllocationType::kReadOnly);
589
590 Tagged<Map> map = roots.swiss_name_dictionary_map();
591 int size = SwissNameDictionary::SizeFor(0);
592 Tagged<HeapObject> obj =
593 AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(size, AllocationType::kReadOnly, map);
594 Tagged<SwissNameDictionary> result = Cast<SwissNameDictionary>(obj);
595 result->Initialize(isolate(), *empty_meta_table, 0);
596 return handle(result, isolate());
597}
598
599// Internalized strings are created in the old generation (data space).
600Handle<String> Factory::InternalizeUtf8String(base::Vector<const char> string) {
601 base::Vector<const uint8_t> utf8_data =
602 base::Vector<const uint8_t>::cast(string);
603 Utf8Decoder decoder(utf8_data);
604 if (decoder.is_ascii()) return InternalizeString(utf8_data);
605 if (decoder.is_one_byte()) {
606 std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> buffer(new uint8_t[decoder.utf16_length()]);
607 decoder.Decode(buffer.get(), utf8_data);
608 return InternalizeString(
609 base::Vector<const uint8_t>(buffer.get(), decoder.utf16_length()));
610 }
611 std::unique_ptr<uint16_t[]> buffer(new uint16_t[decoder.utf16_length()]);
612 decoder.Decode(buffer.get(), utf8_data);
613 return InternalizeString(
614 base::Vector<const base::uc16>(buffer.get(), decoder.utf16_length()));
615}

633void ThrowInvalidEncodedStringBytes(Isolate* isolate, MessageTemplate message) {
634#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
635 DCHECK(message == MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidWtf8 ||
636 message == MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidUtf8);
637 DirectHandle<JSObject> error_obj =
638 isolate->factory()->NewWasmRuntimeError(message);
639 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, error_obj,
640 isolate->factory()->wasm_uncatchable_symbol(),
641 isolate->factory()->true_value(), NONE);
642 isolate->Throw(*error_obj);
643#else
644 // The default in JS-land is to use Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8, which never
645 // throws an error, so if there is no WebAssembly compiled in we'll never get
646 // here.
647 UNREACHABLE();
648#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
649}

651template <typename Decoder, typename PeekBytes>
652MaybeHandle<String> NewStringFromBytes(Isolate* isolate, PeekBytes peek_bytes,
653 AllocationType allocation,
654 MessageTemplate message) {
655 Decoder decoder(peek_bytes());
656 if (decoder.is_invalid()) {
657 if (message != MessageTemplate::kNone) {
658 ThrowInvalidEncodedStringBytes(isolate, message);
659 }
660 return MaybeHandle<String>();
661 }
662
663 if (decoder.utf16_length() == 0) return isolate->factory()->empty_string();
664
665 if (decoder.is_one_byte()) {
666 if (decoder.utf16_length() == 1) {
667 uint8_t codepoint;
668 decoder.Decode(&codepoint, peek_bytes());
669 return isolate->factory()->LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(codepoint);
670 }
671 // Allocate string.
672 Handle<SeqOneByteString> result;
673 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
674 isolate->factory()->NewRawOneByteString(
675 decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
676
677 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
678 decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), peek_bytes());
679 return result;
680 }
681
682 // Allocate string.
683 Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result;
684 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate, result,
685 isolate->factory()->NewRawTwoByteString(
686 decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
687
688 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
689 decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), peek_bytes());
690 return result;
691}

693template <typename PeekBytes>
694MaybeHandle<String> NewStringFromUtf8Variant(Isolate* isolate,
695 PeekBytes peek_bytes,
696 unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant,
697 AllocationType allocation) {
698 switch (utf8_variant) {
699 case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kLossyUtf8:
700 return NewStringFromBytes<Utf8Decoder>(isolate, peek_bytes, allocation,
701 MessageTemplate::kNone);
702#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
703 case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8:
704 return NewStringFromBytes<StrictUtf8Decoder>(
705 isolate, peek_bytes, allocation,
706 MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidUtf8);
707 case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kUtf8NoTrap:
708 return NewStringFromBytes<StrictUtf8Decoder>(
709 isolate, peek_bytes, allocation, MessageTemplate::kNone);
710 case unibrow::Utf8Variant::kWtf8:
711 return NewStringFromBytes<Wtf8Decoder>(
712 isolate, peek_bytes, allocation,
713 MessageTemplate::kWasmTrapStringInvalidWtf8);
714#endif
715 }
716}

720MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8(
721 base::Vector<const uint8_t> string, unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant,
722 AllocationType allocation) {
723 if (string.size() > kMaxInt) {
724 // The Utf8Decode can't handle longer inputs, and we couldn't create
725 // strings from them anyway.
726 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate(), NewInvalidStringLengthError());
727 }
728 auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint8_t> { return string; };
729 return NewStringFromUtf8Variant(isolate(), peek_bytes, utf8_variant,
730 allocation);
731}

739#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
740MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8(
741 DirectHandle<WasmArray> array, uint32_t start, uint32_t end,
742 unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant, AllocationType allocation) {
743 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(uint8_t), array->type()->element_type().value_kind_size());
744 DCHECK_LE(start, end);
745 DCHECK_LE(end, array->length());
746 // {end - start} can never be more than what the Utf8Decoder can handle.
747 static_assert(WasmArray::MaxLength(sizeof(uint8_t)) <= kMaxInt);
748 auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint8_t> {
749 const uint8_t* contents =
750 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(array->ElementAddress(0));
751 return {contents + start, end - start};
752 };
753 return NewStringFromUtf8Variant(isolate(), peek_bytes, utf8_variant,
754 allocation);
755}

757MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8(
758 DirectHandle<ByteArray> array, uint32_t start, uint32_t end,
759 unibrow::Utf8Variant utf8_variant, AllocationType allocation) {
760 DCHECK_LE(start, end);
761 DCHECK_LE(end, array->length());
762 // {end - start} can never be more than what the Utf8Decoder can handle.
763 static_assert(ByteArray::kMaxLength <= kMaxInt);
764 auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint8_t> {
765 const uint8_t* contents = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(array->begin());
766 return {contents + start, end - start};
767 };
768 return NewStringFromUtf8Variant(isolate(), peek_bytes, utf8_variant,
769 allocation);
770}

773struct Wtf16Decoder {
774 int length_;
775 bool is_one_byte_;
776 explicit Wtf16Decoder(base::Vector<const uint16_t> data)
777 : length_(data.length()),
778 is_one_byte_(String::IsOneByte(data.begin(), length_)) {}
779 bool is_invalid() const { return false; }
780 bool is_one_byte() const { return is_one_byte_; }
781 int utf16_length() const { return length_; }
782 template <typename Char>
783 void Decode(Char* out, base::Vector<const uint16_t> data) {
784 CopyChars(out, data.begin(), length_);
785 }
786};
787} // namespace

789MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf16(DirectHandle<WasmArray> array,
790 uint32_t start, uint32_t end,
791 AllocationType allocation) {
792 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(uint16_t), array->type()->element_type().value_kind_size());
793 DCHECK_LE(start, end);
794 DCHECK_LE(end, array->length());
795 // {end - start} can never be more than what the Utf8Decoder can handle.
796 static_assert(WasmArray::MaxLength(sizeof(uint16_t)) <= kMaxInt);
797 auto peek_bytes = [&]() -> base::Vector<const uint16_t> {
798 const uint16_t* contents =
799 reinterpret_cast<const uint16_t*>(array->ElementAddress(0));
800 return {contents + start, end - start};
801 };
802 return NewStringFromBytes<Wtf16Decoder>(isolate(), peek_bytes, allocation,
803 MessageTemplate::kNone);
804}

807MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromUtf8SubString(
808 Handle<SeqOneByteString> str, int begin, int length,
809 AllocationType allocation) {
810 base::Vector<const uint8_t> utf8_data;
811 {
812 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
813 utf8_data =
814 base::Vector<const uint8_t>(str->GetChars(no_gc) + begin, length);
815 }
816 Utf8Decoder decoder(utf8_data);
817
818 if (length == 1) {
819 uint16_t t;
820 // Decode even in the case of length 1 since it can be a bad character.
821 decoder.Decode(&t, utf8_data);
822 return LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(t);
823 }
824
825 if (decoder.is_ascii()) {
826 // If the string is ASCII, we can just make a substring.
827 // TODO(v8): the allocation flag is ignored in this case.
828 return NewSubString(str, begin, begin + length);
829 }
830
831 DCHECK_GT(decoder.utf16_length(), 0);
832
833 if (decoder.is_one_byte()) {
834 // Allocate string.
835 Handle<SeqOneByteString> result;
836 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
837 isolate(), result,
838 NewRawOneByteString(decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
839 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
840 // Update pointer references, since the original string may have moved after
841 // allocation.
842 utf8_data =
843 base::Vector<const uint8_t>(str->GetChars(no_gc) + begin, length);
844 decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), utf8_data);
845 return result;
846 }
847
848 // Allocate string.
849 Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result;
850 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(
851 isolate(), result,
852 NewRawTwoByteString(decoder.utf16_length(), allocation));
853
854 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
855 // Update pointer references, since the original string may have moved after
856 // allocation.
857 utf8_data = base::Vector<const uint8_t>(str->GetChars(no_gc) + begin, length);
858 decoder.Decode(result->GetChars(no_gc), utf8_data);
859 return result;
860}

862MaybeHandle<String> Factory::NewStringFromTwoByte(const base::uc16* string,
863 int length,
864 AllocationType allocation) {
865 DCHECK_NE(allocation, AllocationType::kReadOnly);
866 if (length == 0) return empty_string();
867 if (String::IsOneByte(string, length)) {
868 if (length == 1) return LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(string[0]);
869 Handle<SeqOneByteString> result;
870 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), result,
871 NewRawOneByteString(length, allocation));
872 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
873 CopyChars(result->GetChars(no_gc), string, length);
874 return result;
875 } else {
876 Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result;
877 ASSIGN_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION(isolate(), result,
878 NewRawTwoByteString(length, allocation));
879 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
880 CopyChars(result->GetChars(no_gc), string, length);
881 return result;
882 }
883}

929StringTransitionStrategy Factory::ComputeInternalizationStrategyForString(
930 DirectHandle<String> string, MaybeDirectHandle<Map>* internalized_map) {
931 // The serializer requires internalized strings to be in ReadOnlySpace s.t.
932 // other objects referencing the string can be allocated in RO space
933 // themselves.
934 if (isolate()->enable_ro_allocation_for_snapshot() &&
935 isolate()->serializer_enabled()) {
936 return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
937 }
938 // Do not internalize young strings in-place: This allows us to ignore both
939 // string table and stub cache on scavenges.
940 if (HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*string)) {
941 return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
942 }
943 // If the string table is shared, we need to copy if the string is not already
944 // in the shared heap.
945 if (v8_flags.shared_string_table && !HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*string)) {
946 return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
947 }
948 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(internalized_map);
949 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
950 // This method may be called concurrently, so snapshot the map from the input
951 // string instead of the calling IsType methods on HeapObject, which would
952 // reload the map each time.
953 Tagged<Map> map = string->map();
954 *internalized_map = GetInPlaceInternalizedStringMap(map);
955 if (!internalized_map->is_null()) {
956 return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
957 }
958 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsInternalizedString(map)) {
959 return StringTransitionStrategy::kAlreadyTransitioned;
960 }
961 return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
962}
963
964template <class StringClass>
965Handle<StringClass> Factory::InternalizeExternalString(
966 DirectHandle<String> string) {
967 DirectHandle<Map> map =
968 GetInPlaceInternalizedStringMap(string->map()).ToHandleChecked();
969 Tagged<StringClass> external_string =
970 Cast<StringClass>(New(map, AllocationType::kOld));
971 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
972 external_string->InitExternalPointerFields(isolate());
973 Tagged<StringClass> cast_string = Cast<StringClass>(*string);
974 external_string->set_length(cast_string->length());
975 external_string->set_raw_hash_field(cast_string->raw_hash_field());
976 external_string->SetResource(isolate(), nullptr);
977 isolate()->heap()->RegisterExternalString(external_string);
978 return handle(external_string, isolate());
979}
980
981template Handle<ExternalOneByteString> Factory::InternalizeExternalString<
982 ExternalOneByteString>(DirectHandle<String>);
983template Handle<ExternalTwoByteString> Factory::InternalizeExternalString<
984 ExternalTwoByteString>(DirectHandle<String>);
985
986StringTransitionStrategy Factory::ComputeSharingStrategyForString(
987 DirectHandle<String> string, MaybeDirectHandle<Map>* shared_map) {
988 DCHECK(v8_flags.shared_string_table);
989 // TODO(pthier): Avoid copying LO-space strings. Update page flags instead.
990 if (!HeapLayout::InAnySharedSpace(*string)) {
991 return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
992 }
993 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(shared_map);
994 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
995 InstanceType instance_type = string->map()->instance_type();
996 if (StringShape(instance_type).IsShared()) {
997 return StringTransitionStrategy::kAlreadyTransitioned;
998 }
999 switch (instance_type) {
1000 case SEQ_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1001 *shared_map = shared_seq_two_byte_string_map();
1002 return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1003 case SEQ_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1004 *shared_map = shared_seq_one_byte_string_map();
1005 return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1006 case EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1007 *shared_map = shared_external_two_byte_string_map();
1008 return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1009 case EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1010 *shared_map = shared_external_one_byte_string_map();
1011 return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1012 case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_TWO_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1013 *shared_map = shared_uncached_external_two_byte_string_map();
1014 return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1015 case UNCACHED_EXTERNAL_ONE_BYTE_STRING_TYPE:
1016 *shared_map = shared_uncached_external_one_byte_string_map();
1017 return StringTransitionStrategy::kInPlace;
1018 default:
1019 return StringTransitionStrategy::kCopy;
1020 }
1021}

1023Handle<String> Factory::NewSurrogatePairString(uint16_t lead, uint16_t trail) {
1024 DCHECK_GE(lead, 0xD800);
1025 DCHECK_LE(lead, 0xDBFF);
1026 DCHECK_GE(trail, 0xDC00);
1027 DCHECK_LE(trail, 0xDFFF);

1030 isolate()->factory()->NewRawTwoByteString(2).ToHandleChecked();
1031 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;

1033 dest[0] = lead;
1034 dest[1] = trail;
1035 return str;

1038Handle<String> Factory::NewCopiedSubstring(DirectHandle<String> str,
1039 uint32_t begin, uint32_t length) {
1040 DCHECK(str->IsFlat()); // Callers must flatten.
1041 DCHECK_GT(length, 0); // Callers must handle empty string.
1042 bool one_byte;
1043 {
1044 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1045 String::FlatContent flat = str->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
1046 if (flat.IsOneByte()) {
1047 one_byte = true;
1048 } else {
1049 one_byte = String::IsOneByte(flat.ToUC16Vector().data() + begin, length);
1050 }
1051 }
1052 if (one_byte) {
1053 Handle<SeqOneByteString> result =
1054 NewRawOneByteString(length).ToHandleChecked();
1055 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1056 uint8_t* dest = result->GetChars(no_gc);
1057 String::WriteToFlat(*str, dest, begin, length);
1058 return result;
1059 } else {
1060 Handle<SeqTwoByteString> result =
1061 NewRawTwoByteString(length).ToHandleChecked();
1062 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1063 base::uc16* dest = result->GetChars(no_gc);
1064 String::WriteToFlat(*str, dest, begin, length);
1065 return result;
1066 }
1067}

1069Handle<String> Factory::NewProperSubString(DirectHandle<String> str,
1070 uint32_t begin, uint32_t end) {
1071#if VERIFY_HEAP
1072 if (v8_flags.verify_heap) str->StringVerify(isolate());
1073#endif
1074 DCHECK_LE(begin, str->length());
1075 DCHECK_LE(end, str->length());
1076
1077 str = String::Flatten(isolate(), str);
1078
1079 if (begin >= end) return empty_string();
1080 uint32_t length = end - begin;
1081
1082 if (length == 1) {
1083 return LookupSingleCharacterStringFromCode(str->Get(begin));
1084 }
1085 if (length == 2) {
1086 // Optimization for 2-byte strings often used as keys in a decompression
1087 // dictionary. Check whether we already have the string in the string
1088 // table to prevent creation of many unnecessary strings.
1089 uint16_t c1 = str->Get(begin);
1090 uint16_t c2 = str->Get(begin + 1);
1091 return MakeOrFindTwoCharacterString(c1, c2);
1092 }
1093
1094 if (!v8_flags.string_slices || length < SlicedString::kMinLength) {
1095 return NewCopiedSubstring(str, begin, length);
1096 }
1097
1098 int offset = begin;
1099
1100 if (IsSlicedString(*str)) {
1101 auto slice = Cast<SlicedString>(str);
1102 str = direct_handle(slice->parent(), isolate());
1103 offset += slice->offset();
1104 }
1105 if (IsThinString(*str)) {
1106 auto thin = Cast<ThinString>(str);
1107 str = direct_handle(thin->actual(), isolate());
1108 }
1109
1110 DCHECK(IsSeqString(*str) || IsExternalString(*str));
1111 DirectHandle<Map> map = str->IsOneByteRepresentation()
1112 ? sliced_one_byte_string_map()
1113 : sliced_two_byte_string_map();
1114 Tagged<SlicedString> slice =
1115 Cast<SlicedString>(New(map, AllocationType::kYoung));
1116 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1117 slice->set_raw_hash_field(String::kEmptyHashField);
1118 slice->set_length(length);
1119 slice->set_parent(*str);
1120 slice->set_offset(offset);
1121 return handle(slice, isolate());
1122}

1186Tagged<Symbol> Factory::NewSymbolInternal(AllocationType allocation) {
1187 DCHECK(allocation != AllocationType::kYoung);
1188 // Statically ensure that it is safe to allocate symbols in paged spaces.
1189 static_assert(sizeof(Symbol) <= kMaxRegularHeapObjectSize);
1190
1191 Tagged<Symbol> symbol = Cast<Symbol>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1192 sizeof(Symbol), allocation, read_only_roots().symbol_map()));
1193 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1194 // Generate a random hash value.
1195 int hash = isolate()->GenerateIdentityHash(Name::HashBits::kMax);
1196 symbol->set_raw_hash_field(
1197 Name::CreateHashFieldValue(hash, Name::HashFieldType::kHash));
1198 if (isolate()->read_only_heap()->roots_init_complete()) {
1199 symbol->set_description(read_only_roots().undefined_value(),
1200 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1201 } else {
1202 // Can't use setter during bootstrapping as its typecheck tries to access
1203 // the roots table before it is initialized.
1204 symbol->description_.store(&*symbol, read_only_roots().undefined_value(),
1205 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1206 }
1207 symbol->set_flags(0);
1208 DCHECK(!symbol->is_private());
1209 return symbol;
1210}

1231
1232Tagged<Context> Factory::NewContextInternal(DirectHandle<Map> map, int size,
1233 int variadic_part_length,
1234 AllocationType allocation) {
1235 DCHECK_LE(Context::kTodoHeaderSize, size);
1236 DCHECK(IsAligned(size, kTaggedSize));
1237 DCHECK_LE(Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS, variadic_part_length);
1238 DCHECK_LE(Context::SizeFor(variadic_part_length), size);
1239
1240 Tagged<HeapObject> result =
1241 allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(size,
1242 allocation);
1243 result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map);
1244 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1245 Tagged<Context> context = Cast<Context>(result);
1246 context->set_length(variadic_part_length);
1247 DCHECK_EQ(context->SizeFromMap(*map), size);
1248 if (size > Context::kTodoHeaderSize) {
1249 ObjectSlot start = context->RawField(Context::kTodoHeaderSize);
1250 ObjectSlot end = context->RawField(size);
1251 size_t slot_count = end - start;
1252 MemsetTagged(start, *undefined_value(), slot_count);
1253 }
1254 return context;
1255}
1256
1257// Creates new maps and new native context and wires them up.
1258//
1259// +-+------------->|NativeContext|
1260// | | |
1261// | | map
1262// | | v
1263// | | |context_map| <Map(NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE)>
1264// | | | |
1265// | +--native_context--+ map
1266// | v
1267// | +------->|contextful_meta_map| <Map(MAP_TYPE)>
1268// | | | |
1269// | +-----map-----+ |
1270// | |
1271// +-----native_context-----+
1272//
1273Handle<NativeContext> Factory::NewNativeContext() {
1274 // All maps that belong to this new native context will have this meta map.
1275 // The native context does not exist yet, so create the map as contextless
1276 // for now.
1277 DirectHandle<Map> contextful_meta_map =
1278 NewContextlessMap(MAP_TYPE, Map::kSize);
1279 contextful_meta_map->set_map(isolate(), *contextful_meta_map);
1280
1281 DirectHandle<Map> context_map = NewMapWithMetaMap(
1282 contextful_meta_map, NATIVE_CONTEXT_TYPE, kVariableSizeSentinel);
1283
1284 if (v8_flags.log_maps) {
1285 LOG(isolate(),
1286 MapEvent("NewNativeContext", isolate()->factory()->meta_map(),
1287 contextful_meta_map, "contextful meta map"));
1288 LOG(isolate(),
1289 MapEvent("NewNativeContext", isolate()->factory()->meta_map(),
1290 context_map, "native context map"));
1291 }
1292
1293 Tagged<NativeContext> context = Cast<NativeContext>(NewContextInternal(
1294 context_map, NativeContext::kSize, NativeContext::NATIVE_CONTEXT_SLOTS,
1295 AllocationType::kOld));
1296 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1297 contextful_meta_map->set_native_context(context);
1298 context_map->set_native_context(context);
1299 context->set_meta_map(*contextful_meta_map);
1300 context->set_scope_info(*native_scope_info());
1301 context->set_previous(Context());
1302 context->set_extension(*undefined_value());
1303 context->set_errors_thrown(Smi::zero());
1304 context->set_is_wasm_js_installed(Smi::zero());
1305 context->set_is_wasm_jspi_installed(Smi::zero());
1306 context->set_math_random_index(Smi::zero());
1307 context->set_serialized_objects(*empty_fixed_array());
1308 context->init_microtask_queue(isolate(), nullptr);
1309 context->set_retained_maps(*empty_weak_array_list());
1310 return handle(context, isolate());
1311}

1520void Factory::ProcessNewScript(DirectHandle<Script> script,
1521 ScriptEventType script_event_type) {
1522 int script_id = script->id();
1523 if (script_id != Script::kTemporaryScriptId) {
1524 Handle<WeakArrayList> scripts = script_list();
1525 scripts = WeakArrayList::Append(isolate(), scripts,
1526 MaybeObjectDirectHandle::Weak(script),
1527 AllocationType::kOld);
1528 isolate()->heap()->set_script_list(*scripts);
1529 }
1530 if (IsString(script->source()) && isolate()->NeedsSourcePositions()) {
1531 Script::InitLineEnds(isolate(), script);
1532 }
1533 LOG(isolate(), ScriptEvent(script_event_type, script_id));
1534}
1535
1536Handle<Script> Factory::CloneScript(DirectHandle<Script> script,
1537 DirectHandle<String> source) {
1538 int script_id = isolate()->GetNextScriptId();
1539#ifdef V8_SCRIPTORMODULE_LEGACY_LIFETIME
1540 Handle<ArrayList> list = ArrayList::New(isolate(), 0);
1541#endif
1542 Handle<Script> new_script_handle =
1543 Cast<Script>(NewStruct(SCRIPT_TYPE, AllocationType::kOld));
1544 {
1545 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1546 Tagged<Script> new_script = *new_script_handle;
1547 const Tagged<Script> old_script = *script;
1548 new_script->set_source(*source);
1549 new_script->set_name(old_script->name());
1550 new_script->set_id(script_id);
1551 new_script->set_line_offset(old_script->line_offset());
1552 new_script->set_column_offset(old_script->column_offset());
1553 new_script->set_context_data(old_script->context_data());
1554 new_script->set_type(old_script->type());
1555 new_script->set_line_ends(Smi::zero());
1556 new_script->set_eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments(
1557 script->eval_from_shared_or_wrapped_arguments());
1558 new_script->set_infos(*empty_weak_fixed_array(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1559 new_script->set_eval_from_position(old_script->eval_from_position());
1560 new_script->set_flags(old_script->flags());
1561 new_script->set_host_defined_options(old_script->host_defined_options());
1562 new_script->set_source_hash(*undefined_value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1563 new_script->set_compiled_lazy_function_positions(*undefined_value(),
1564 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
1565#ifdef V8_SCRIPTORMODULE_LEGACY_LIFETIME
1566 new_script->set_script_or_modules(*list);
1567#endif
1568 }
1569 ProcessNewScript(new_script_handle, ScriptEventType::kCreate);
1570 return new_script_handle;
1571}

1640Handle<WasmDispatchTable> Factory::NewWasmDispatchTable(
1641 int length, wasm::CanonicalValueType table_type) {
1642 CHECK_LE(length, WasmDispatchTable::kMaxLength);
1643
1644 // TODO(jkummerow): Any chance to get a better estimate?
1645 size_t estimated_offheap_size = 0;
1646 DirectHandle<TrustedManaged<WasmDispatchTableData>> offheap_data =
1647 TrustedManaged<WasmDispatchTableData>::From(
1648 isolate(), estimated_offheap_size,
1649 std::make_shared<WasmDispatchTableData>());
1650
1651 int bytes = WasmDispatchTable::SizeFor(length);
1652 Tagged<WasmDispatchTable> result = UncheckedCast<WasmDispatchTable>(
1653 AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(bytes, AllocationType::kTrusted,
1654 read_only_roots().wasm_dispatch_table_map()));

1657 result->WriteField<int>(WasmDispatchTable::kLengthOffset, length);

1659 result->set_protected_offheap_data(*offheap_data);
1660 result->set_protected_uses(*empty_protected_weak_fixed_array());
1661 result->set_table_type(table_type);

1663 result->Clear(i, WasmDispatchTable::kNewEntry);
1664 result->clear_entry_padding(i);
1665 }
1666 return handle(result, isolate());

1668
1669Handle<WasmTypeInfo> Factory::NewWasmTypeInfo(
1670 Address type_address, Handle<Map> opt_parent,
1671 DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> opt_trusted_data,
1672 wasm::ModuleTypeIndex type_index) {
1673 // We pretenure WasmTypeInfo objects for two reasons:
1674 // (1) They are referenced by Maps, which are assumed to be long-lived,
1675 // so pretenuring the WTI is a bit more efficient.
1676 // (2) The object visitors need to read the WasmTypeInfo to find tagged
1677 // fields in Wasm structs; in the middle of a GC cycle that's only
1678 // safe to do if the WTI is in old space.
1679 std::vector<Handle<Object>> supertypes;
1680 if (opt_parent.is_null()) {
1681 supertypes.resize(wasm::kMinimumSupertypeArraySize, undefined_value());
1682 } else {
1683 DirectHandle<WasmTypeInfo> parent_type_info(opt_parent->wasm_type_info(),
1684 isolate());
1685 int first_undefined_index = -1;
1686 for (int i = 0; i < parent_type_info->supertypes_length(); i++) {
1687 Handle<Object> supertype =
1688 handle(parent_type_info->supertypes(i), isolate());
1689 if (IsUndefined(*supertype) && first_undefined_index == -1) {
1690 first_undefined_index = i;
1691 }
1692 supertypes.emplace_back(supertype);
1693 }
1694 if (first_undefined_index >= 0) {
1695 supertypes[first_undefined_index] = opt_parent;
1696 } else {
1697 supertypes.emplace_back(opt_parent);
1698 }
1699 }
1700 Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_type_info_map();
1701 Tagged<WasmTypeInfo> result = Cast<WasmTypeInfo>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1702 WasmTypeInfo::SizeFor(static_cast<int>(supertypes.size())),
1703 AllocationType::kOld, map));
1704 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1705 result->set_supertypes_length(static_cast<int>(supertypes.size()));
1706 for (size_t i = 0; i < supertypes.size(); i++) {
1707 result->set_supertypes(static_cast<int>(i), *supertypes[i]);
1708 }
1709 result->init_native_type(isolate(), type_address);
1710 if (opt_trusted_data.is_null()) {
1711 result->clear_trusted_data();
1712 } else {
1713 result->set_trusted_data(*opt_trusted_data);
1714 }
1715 result->set_module_type_index(type_index.index);
1716 return handle(result, isolate());
1717}
1718
1719Handle<WasmImportData> Factory::NewWasmImportData(
1720 DirectHandle<HeapObject> callable, wasm::Suspend suspend,
1721 MaybeDirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance_data,
1722 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig) {
1723 Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_import_data_map();
1724 auto result = Cast<WasmImportData>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1725 map->instance_size(), AllocationType::kTrusted, map));
1726 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1727 result->set_native_context(*isolate()->native_context());
1728 result->set_callable(Cast<UnionOf<Undefined, JSReceiver>>(*callable));
1729 result->set_suspend(suspend);
1730 if (instance_data.is_null()) {
1731 result->clear_instance_data();
1732 } else {
1733 result->set_instance_data(*instance_data.ToHandleChecked());
1734 }
1735 result->set_wrapper_budget(v8_flags.wasm_wrapper_tiering_budget);
1736 result->clear_call_origin();
1737 result->set_sig(sig);
1738#if TAGGED_SIZE_8_BYTES
1739 result->set_optional_padding(0);
1740#endif
1741 return handle(result, isolate());
1742}

1798Handle<WasmJSFunctionData> Factory::NewWasmJSFunctionData(
1799 wasm::CanonicalTypeIndex sig_index, DirectHandle<JSReceiver> callable,
1800 DirectHandle<Code> wrapper_code, DirectHandle<Map> rtt,
1801 wasm::Suspend suspend, wasm::Promise promise) {
1802 // TODO(clemensb): Should this be passed instead of looked up here?
1803 const wasm::CanonicalSig* sig =
1804 wasm::GetTypeCanonicalizer()->LookupFunctionSignature(sig_index);
1805 DirectHandle<WasmImportData> import_data = NewWasmImportData(
1806 callable, suspend, DirectHandle<WasmTrustedInstanceData>(), sig);
1807
1808 // Rough guess for a wrapper that may be shared with other users of it.
1809 constexpr size_t kOffheapDataSizeEstimate = 100;
1810 DirectHandle<TrustedManaged<WasmJSFunctionData::OffheapData>> offheap_data =
1811 TrustedManaged<WasmJSFunctionData::OffheapData>::From(
1812 isolate(), kOffheapDataSizeEstimate,
1813 std::make_shared<WasmJSFunctionData::OffheapData>(
1814 sig->signature_hash()));
1815
1816 DirectHandle<WasmInternalFunction> internal =
1817 NewWasmInternalFunction(import_data, -1);
1818 DirectHandle<WasmFuncRef> func_ref = NewWasmFuncRef(internal, rtt);
1819 import_data->SetFuncRefAsCallOrigin(*internal);
1820 Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_js_function_data_map();
1821 Tagged<WasmJSFunctionData> result =
1822 Cast<WasmJSFunctionData>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1823 map->instance_size(), AllocationType::kTrusted, map));
1824 result->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());
1825 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1826 result->set_func_ref(*func_ref);
1827 result->set_internal(*internal);
1828 result->set_wrapper_code(*wrapper_code);
1829 result->set_canonical_sig_index(sig_index.index);
1830 result->set_js_promise_flags(WasmFunctionData::SuspendField::encode(suspend) |
1831 WasmFunctionData::PromiseField::encode(promise));
1832 result->set_protected_offheap_data(*offheap_data);
1833 return handle(result, isolate());
1834}

1848Handle<WasmSuspenderObject> Factory::NewWasmSuspenderObject() {
1849 DirectHandle<JSPromise> promise = NewJSPromise();
1850 Tagged<Map> map = *wasm_suspender_object_map();
1851 Tagged<WasmSuspenderObject> obj =
1852 Cast<WasmSuspenderObject>(AllocateRawWithImmortalMap(
1853 map->instance_size(), AllocationType::kOld, map));
1854 auto suspender = handle(obj, isolate());
1855 // Ensure that all properties are initialized before the allocation below.
1856 suspender->set_continuation(*undefined_value());
1857 suspender->set_parent(*undefined_value());
1858 suspender->set_promise(*promise);
1859 suspender->set_resume(*undefined_value());
1860 suspender->set_reject(*undefined_value());
1861 suspender->set_state(WasmSuspenderObject::kInactive);
1862 // Instantiate the callable object which resumes this Suspender. This will be
1863 // used implicitly as the onFulfilled callback of the returned JS promise.
1864 DirectHandle<WasmResumeData> resume_data =
1865 NewWasmResumeData(suspender, wasm::OnResume::kContinue);
1866 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> resume_sfi =
1867 NewSharedFunctionInfoForWasmResume(resume_data);
1868 DirectHandle<Context> context(isolate()->native_context());
1869 DirectHandle<JSObject> resume =
1870 Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate(), resume_sfi, context}.Build();
1871
1872 DirectHandle<WasmResumeData> reject_data =
1873 isolate()->factory()->NewWasmResumeData(suspender,
1874 wasm::OnResume::kThrow);
1875 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> reject_sfi =
1876 isolate()->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForWasmResume(reject_data);
1877 DirectHandle<JSObject> reject =
1878 Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate(), reject_sfi, context}.Build();
1879 suspender->set_resume(*resume);
1880 suspender->set_reject(*reject);
1881 return suspender;
1882}

1963Handle<WasmArray> Factory::NewWasmArray(wasm::ValueType element_type,
1964 uint32_t length,
1965 wasm::WasmValue initial_value,
1966 DirectHandle<Map> map) {
1967 Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
1968 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1969 if (element_type.is_numeric()) {
1970 if (initial_value.zero_byte_representation()) {
1971 memset(reinterpret_cast<void*>(result->ElementAddress(0)), 0,
1972 length * element_type.value_kind_size());
1973 } else {
1974 wasm::WasmValue packed = initial_value.Packed(element_type);
1975 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
1976 Address address = result->ElementAddress(i);
1977 packed.CopyTo(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(address));
1978 }
1979 }
1980 } else {
1981 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
1982 result->SetTaggedElement(i, initial_value.to_ref());
1983 }
1984 }
1985 return handle(result, isolate());
1986}

1988Handle<WasmArray> Factory::NewWasmArrayFromElements(
1989 const wasm::ArrayType* type, base::Vector<wasm::WasmValue> elements,
1990 DirectHandle<Map> map) {
1991 uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(elements.size());
1992 Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
1993 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1994 if (type->element_type().is_numeric()) {
1995 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
1996 Address address = result->ElementAddress(i);
1997 elements[i]
1998 .Packed(type->element_type())
1999 .CopyTo(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(address));
2000 }
2001 } else {
2002 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2003 result->SetTaggedElement(i, elements[i].to_ref());
2004 }
2005 }
2006 return handle(result, isolate());
2007}

2009Handle<WasmArray> Factory::NewWasmArrayFromMemory(uint32_t length,
2010 DirectHandle<Map> map,
2011 Address source) {
2012 wasm::ValueType element_type =
2013 reinterpret_cast<wasm::ArrayType*>(map->wasm_type_info()->native_type())
2014 ->element_type();
2015 DCHECK(element_type.is_numeric());
2016 Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
2017 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2018#if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
2019 MemCopyAndSwitchEndianness(reinterpret_cast<void*>(result->ElementAddress(0)),
2020 reinterpret_cast<void*>(source), length,
2021 element_type.value_kind_size());
2022#else
2023 MemCopy(reinterpret_cast<void*>(result->ElementAddress(0)),
2024 reinterpret_cast<void*>(source),
2025 length * element_type.value_kind_size());
2026#endif
2027
2028 return handle(result, isolate());
2029}

2031Handle<Object> Factory::NewWasmArrayFromElementSegment(
2032 Handle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> trusted_instance_data,
2033 Handle<WasmTrustedInstanceData> shared_trusted_instance_data,
2034 uint32_t segment_index, uint32_t start_offset, uint32_t length,
2035 DirectHandle<Map> map) {
2036 DCHECK(WasmArray::type(*map)->element_type().is_reference());
2037
2038 // If the element segment has not been initialized yet, lazily initialize it
2039 // now.
2040 AccountingAllocator allocator;
2041 Zone zone(&allocator, ZONE_NAME);
2042 std::optional<MessageTemplate> opt_error = wasm::InitializeElementSegment(
2043 &zone, isolate(), trusted_instance_data, shared_trusted_instance_data,
2044 segment_index);
2045 if (opt_error.has_value()) {
2046 return handle(Smi::FromEnum(opt_error.value()), isolate());
2047 }
2048
2049 DirectHandle<FixedArray> elements = direct_handle(
2050 Cast<FixedArray>(
2051 trusted_instance_data->element_segments()->get(segment_index)),
2052 isolate());
2053
2054 Tagged<WasmArray> result = NewWasmArrayUninitialized(length, map);
2055 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2056 if (length > 0) {
2057 isolate()->heap()->CopyRange(result, result->ElementSlot(0),
2058 elements->RawFieldOfElementAt(start_offset),
2059 length, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2060 }
2061 return handle(result, isolate());
2062}

2076Handle<WasmStruct> Factory::NewWasmStruct(const wasm::StructType* type,
2077 wasm::WasmValue* args,
2078 DirectHandle<Map> map) {
2079 Tagged<HeapObject> raw =
2080 AllocateRaw(WasmStruct::Size(type), AllocationType::kYoung);
2081 raw->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map);
2082 Tagged<WasmStruct> result = Cast<WasmStruct>(raw);
2083 result->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*empty_fixed_array(), kRelaxedStore);
2084 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < type->field_count(); i++) {
2085 int offset = type->field_offset(i);
2086 if (type->field(i).is_numeric()) {
2087 Address address = result->RawFieldAddress(offset);
2088 args[i]
2089 .Packed(type->field(i))
2090 .CopyTo(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(address));
2091 } else {
2092 offset += WasmStruct::kHeaderSize;
2093 TaggedField<Object>::store(result, offset, *args[i].to_ref());
2094 }
2095 }
2096 return handle(result, isolate());
2097}

2236Handle<TransitionArray> Factory::NewTransitionArray(int number_of_transitions,
2237 int slack) {
2238 int capacity = TransitionArray::LengthFor(number_of_transitions + slack);
2239 Handle<TransitionArray> array = Cast<TransitionArray>(
2240 NewWeakFixedArrayWithMap(read_only_roots().transition_array_map(),
2241 capacity, AllocationType::kOld));
2242 // Transition arrays are AllocationType::kOld. When black allocation is on we
2243 // have to add the transition array to the list of
2244 // encountered_transition_arrays.
2245 Heap* heap = isolate()->heap();
2246 if (heap->incremental_marking()->black_allocation()) {
2247 heap->mark_compact_collector()->AddTransitionArray(*array);
2248 }
2249 array->WeakFixedArray::set(TransitionArray::kPrototypeTransitionsIndex,
2250 Smi::zero());
2251 array->WeakFixedArray::set(TransitionArray::kSideStepTransitionsIndex,
2252 Smi::zero());
2253 array->WeakFixedArray::set(TransitionArray::kTransitionLengthIndex,
2254 Smi::FromInt(number_of_transitions));
2255 return array;
2256}

2258Handle<AllocationSite> Factory::NewAllocationSite(bool with_weak_next) {

2260 ? allocation_site_map()
2261 : allocation_site_without_weaknext_map();

2274template <typename MetaMapProviderFunc>
2275Handle<Map> Factory::NewMapImpl(MetaMapProviderFunc&& meta_map_provider,
2276 InstanceType type, int instance_size,
2277 ElementsKind elements_kind,
2278 int inobject_properties,
2279 AllocationType allocation_type) {
2280 static_assert(LAST_JS_OBJECT_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
2281 DCHECK(!InstanceTypeChecker::MayHaveMapCheckFastCase(type));
2282 DCHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(type) &&
2283 !Map::CanHaveFastTransitionableElementsKind(type),
2284 IsDictionaryElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
2285 IsTerminalElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
2286 IsSharedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind));
2287 DCHECK(allocation_type == AllocationType::kMap ||
2288 allocation_type == AllocationType::kSharedMap);
2289 Tagged<HeapObject> result =
2290 allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
2291 Map::kSize, allocation_type);
2292 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2293 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
2294 result->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), meta_map_provider());
2295
2296#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
2297 CHECK_IMPLIES(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(type),
2298 V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(result.ptr()) >
2299 InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit);
2300#endif
2301 isolate()->counters()->maps_created()->Increment();
2302 return handle(InitializeMap(Cast<Map>(result), type, instance_size,
2303 elements_kind, inobject_properties, roots),
2304 isolate());
2305}
2306
2307Tagged<Map> Factory::InitializeMap(Tagged<Map> map, InstanceType type,
2308 int instance_size,
2309 ElementsKind elements_kind,
2310 int inobject_properties,
2311 ReadOnlyRoots roots) {
2312 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2313 map->set_bit_field(0);
2314 map->set_bit_field2(Map::Bits2::NewTargetIsBaseBit::encode(true));
2315 int bit_field3 =
2316 Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::encode(kInvalidEnumCacheSentinel) |
2317 Map::Bits3::OwnsDescriptorsBit::encode(true) |
2318 Map::Bits3::ConstructionCounterBits::encode(Map::kNoSlackTracking) |
2319 Map::Bits3::IsExtensibleBit::encode(true);
2320 map->set_bit_field3(bit_field3);
2321 map->set_instance_type(type);
2322 map->init_prototype_and_constructor_or_back_pointer(roots);
2323 map->set_instance_size(instance_size);
2324 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(type)) {
2325 // Shared space JS objects have fixed layout and can have RO maps. No other
2326 // JS objects have RO maps.
2327 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObjectMap(*map),
2328 !ReadOnlyHeap::Contains(map));
2329 map->SetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords(instance_size / kTaggedSize -
2330 inobject_properties);
2331 DCHECK_EQ(map->GetInObjectProperties(), inobject_properties);
2332 map->set_prototype_validity_cell(roots.invalid_prototype_validity_cell(),
2333 kRelaxedStore);
2334 } else {
2335 DCHECK_EQ(inobject_properties, 0);
2336 map->set_inobject_properties_start_or_constructor_function_index(0);
2337 map->set_prototype_validity_cell(Map::kPrototypeChainValidSmi,
2338 kRelaxedStore, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2339 }
2340 map->set_dependent_code(DependentCode::empty_dependent_code(roots),
2341 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2342 map->set_raw_transitions(Smi::zero(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2343 map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(inobject_properties);
2344 map->SetInstanceDescriptors(isolate(), roots.empty_descriptor_array(), 0,
2345 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2346 // Must be called only after |instance_type| and |instance_size| are set.
2347 map->set_visitor_id(Map::GetVisitorId(map));
2348 DCHECK(!map->is_in_retained_map_list());
2349 map->clear_padding();
2350 map->set_elements_kind(elements_kind);
2351 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.log_maps)) {
2352 LOG(isolate(), MapCreate(map));
2353 }
2354 return map;
2355}

2459
2460Handle<JSObject> Factory::CopyJSObjectWithAllocationSite(
2461 DirectHandle<JSObject> source, DirectHandle<AllocationSite> site) {
2462 DirectHandle<Map> map(source->map(), isolate());
2463
2464 // We can only clone regexps, normal objects, api objects, errors or arrays.
2465 // Copying anything else will break invariants.
2466 InstanceType instance_type = map->instance_type();
2467 bool is_clonable_js_type =
2468 instance_type == JS_REG_EXP_TYPE || instance_type == JS_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2469 instance_type == JS_ERROR_TYPE || instance_type == JS_ARRAY_TYPE ||
2470 instance_type == JS_SPECIAL_API_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2471 InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(instance_type);
2472 bool is_clonable_wasm_type = false;
2473#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2474 is_clonable_wasm_type = instance_type == WASM_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2475 instance_type == WASM_INSTANCE_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2476 instance_type == WASM_MEMORY_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2477 instance_type == WASM_MODULE_OBJECT_TYPE ||
2478 instance_type == WASM_TABLE_OBJECT_TYPE;
2479#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2480 CHECK(is_clonable_js_type || is_clonable_wasm_type);
2481
2482 DCHECK(site.is_null() || AllocationSite::CanTrack(instance_type));
2483
2484 int object_size = map->instance_size();
2485 int aligned_object_size = ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(object_size);
2486 int adjusted_object_size = aligned_object_size;
2487 if (!site.is_null()) {
2488 DCHECK(V8_ALLOCATION_SITE_TRACKING_BOOL);
2489 adjusted_object_size +=
2490 ALIGN_TO_ALLOCATION_ALIGNMENT(AllocationMemento::kSize);
2491 }
2492 Tagged<HeapObject> raw_clone =
2493 allocator()->AllocateRawWith<HeapAllocator::kRetryOrFail>(
2494 adjusted_object_size, AllocationType::kYoung);
2495
2496 DCHECK_NEWLY_ALLOCATED_OBJECT_IS_YOUNG(isolate(), raw_clone);
2497
2498 Heap::CopyBlock(raw_clone.address(), source->address(), object_size);
2499 Handle<JSObject> clone(Cast<JSObject>(raw_clone), isolate());
2500
2501 if (v8_flags.enable_unconditional_write_barriers) {
2502 // By default, we shouldn't need to update the write barrier here, as the
2503 // clone will be allocated in new space.
2504 const ObjectSlot start(raw_clone.address());
2505 const ObjectSlot end(raw_clone.address() + object_size);
2506 WriteBarrier::ForRange(isolate()->heap(), raw_clone, start, end);
2507 }
2508 if (!site.is_null()) {
2509 Tagged<AllocationMemento> alloc_memento = UncheckedCast<AllocationMemento>(
2510 Tagged<Object>(raw_clone.ptr() + aligned_object_size));
2511 InitializeAllocationMemento(alloc_memento, *site);
2512 }
2513
2514 SLOW_DCHECK(clone->GetElementsKind() == source->GetElementsKind());
2515 Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elements = source->elements();
2516 // Update elements if necessary.
2517 if (elements->length() > 0) {
2518 Tagged<FixedArrayBase> elem;
2519 if (elements->map() == *fixed_cow_array_map()) {
2520 elem = elements;
2521 } else if (source->HasDoubleElements()) {
2522 elem = *CopyFixedDoubleArray(
2523 handle(Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(elements), isolate()));
2524 } else {
2525 elem = *CopyFixedArray(handle(Cast<FixedArray>(elements), isolate()));
2526 }
2527 clone->set_elements(elem);
2528 }
2529
2530 // Update properties if necessary.
2531 if (source->HasFastProperties()) {
2532 Tagged<PropertyArray> properties = source->property_array();
2533 if (properties->length() > 0) {
2534 // TODO(gsathya): Do not copy hash code.
2535 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> prop =
2536 CopyArrayWithMap(direct_handle(properties, isolate()),
2537 direct_handle(properties->map(), isolate()));
2538 clone->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*prop, kRelaxedStore);
2539 }
2540 } else {
2541 DirectHandle<Object> copied_properties;
2542 if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
2543 copied_properties = SwissNameDictionary::ShallowCopy(
2544 isolate(),
2545 direct_handle(source->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate()));
2546 } else {
2547 copied_properties =
2548 CopyFixedArray(handle(source->property_dictionary(), isolate()));
2549 }
2550 clone->set_raw_properties_or_hash(*copied_properties, kRelaxedStore);
2551 }
2552 return clone;
2553}

2575template <typename T>
2576Handle<T> Factory::CopyArrayWithMap(DirectHandle<T> src, DirectHandle<Map> map,
2577 AllocationType allocation) {
2578 int len = src->length();
2579 Tagged<HeapObject> new_object = AllocateRawFixedArray(len, allocation);
2580 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2581 new_object->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), *map, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2582 Tagged<T> result = Cast<T>(new_object);
2583 initialize_length(result, len);
2584 // Copy the content.
2585 WriteBarrierMode mode = result->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2586 T::CopyElements(isolate(), result, 0, *src, 0, len, mode);
2587 return handle(result, isolate());
2588}

2590template <typename T>
2591Handle<T> Factory::CopyArrayAndGrow(DirectHandle<T> src, int grow_by,
2592 AllocationType allocation) {
2593 DCHECK_LT(0, grow_by);
2594 DCHECK_LE(grow_by, kMaxInt - src->length());
2595 int old_len = src->length();
2596 int new_len = old_len + grow_by;
2597 // TODO(jgruber,v8:14345): Use T::Allocate instead.
2598 Tagged<HeapObject> new_object = AllocateRawFixedArray(new_len, allocation);
2599 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2600 new_object->set_map_after_allocation(isolate(), src->map(),
2601 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
2602 Tagged<T> result = Cast<T>(new_object);
2603 initialize_length(result, new_len);
2604 // Copy the content.
2605 WriteBarrierMode mode = result->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2606 T::CopyElements(isolate(), result, 0, *src, 0, old_len, mode);
2607 // TODO(jgruber,v8:14345): Enable the static assert once all T's support it:
2608 // static_assert(T::kElementSize == kTaggedSize);
2609 MemsetTagged(ObjectSlot(result->RawFieldOfElementAt(old_len)),
2610 read_only_roots().undefined_value(), grow_by);
2611 return handle(result, isolate());
2612}

2681Handle<WeakArrayList> Factory::CompactWeakArrayList(
2682 DirectHandle<WeakArrayList> src, int new_capacity,
2683 AllocationType allocation) {
2684 Handle<WeakArrayList> result =
2685 NewUninitializedWeakArrayList(new_capacity, allocation);
2686
2687 // Copy the content.
2688 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2689 Tagged<WeakArrayList> raw_src = *src;
2690 Tagged<WeakArrayList> raw_result = *result;
2691 WriteBarrierMode mode = raw_result->GetWriteBarrierMode(no_gc);
2692 int copy_to = 0, length = raw_src->length();
2693 for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
2694 Tagged<MaybeObject> element = raw_src->Get(i);
2695 if (element.IsCleared()) continue;
2696 raw_result->Set(copy_to++, element, mode);
2697 }
2698 raw_result->set_length(copy_to);
2699
2700 MemsetTagged(ObjectSlot(raw_result->data_start() + copy_to),
2701 read_only_roots().undefined_value(), new_capacity - copy_to);
2702 return result;
2703}

2833Handle<JSObject> Factory::NewFunctionPrototype(
2834 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function) {
2835 // Make sure to use globals from the function's context, since the function
2836 // can be from a different context.
2837 DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context(function->native_context(),
2838 isolate());
2839 DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
2840 if (V8_UNLIKELY(IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function->shared()->kind()))) {
2841 new_map = direct_handle(
2842 native_context->async_generator_object_prototype_map(), isolate());
2843 } else if (IsResumableFunction(function->shared()->kind())) {
2844 // Generator and async function prototypes can share maps since they
2845 // don't have "constructor" properties.
2846 new_map = direct_handle(native_context->generator_object_prototype_map(),
2847 isolate());
2848 } else {
2849 // Each function prototype gets a fresh map to avoid unwanted sharing of
2850 // maps between prototypes of different constructors.
2851 DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(native_context->object_function(),
2852 isolate());
2853 DCHECK(object_function->has_initial_map());
2854 new_map = direct_handle(object_function->initial_map(), isolate());
2855 }
2856
2857 DCHECK(!new_map->is_prototype_map());
2858 Handle<JSObject> prototype = NewJSObjectFromMap(new_map);
2859
2860 if (!IsResumableFunction(function->shared()->kind())) {
2861 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), prototype, constructor_string(), function,
2862 DONT_ENUM);
2863 }
2864
2865 return prototype;
2866}

2923 DirectHandle<BytecodeArray> source) {

2930 copy->init_self_indirect_pointer(isolate());

2933 copy->set_parameter_count(raw_source->parameter_count());
2934 copy->set_max_arguments(raw_source->max_arguments());
2935 copy->set_incoming_new_target_or_generator_register(
2936 raw_source->incoming_new_target_or_generator_register());
2937 copy->set_constant_pool(raw_source->constant_pool());
2938 copy->set_handler_table(raw_source->handler_table());
2939 copy->set_wrapper(*wrapper);

2978Handle<JSGlobalObject> Factory::NewJSGlobalObject(
2979 DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor) {
2980 DCHECK(constructor->has_initial_map());
2981 DirectHandle<Map> map(constructor->initial_map(), isolate());
2982 DCHECK(map->is_dictionary_map());
2983
2984 // Make sure no field properties are described in the initial map.
2985 // This guarantees us that normalizing the properties does not
2986 // require us to change property values to PropertyCells.
2987 DCHECK_EQ(map->NextFreePropertyIndex(), 0);
2988
2989 // Make sure we don't have a ton of pre-allocated slots in the
2990 // global objects. They will be unused once we normalize the object.
2991 DCHECK_EQ(map->UnusedPropertyFields(), 0);
2992 DCHECK_EQ(map->GetInObjectProperties(), 0);
2993
2994 // Initial size of the backing store to avoid resize of the storage during
2995 // bootstrapping. The size differs between the JS global object ad the
2996 // builtins object.
2997 int initial_size = 64;
2998
2999 // Allocate a dictionary object for backing storage.
3000 int at_least_space_for = map->NumberOfOwnDescriptors() * 2 + initial_size;
3001 Handle<GlobalDictionary> dictionary =
3002 GlobalDictionary::New(isolate(), at_least_space_for);
3003
3004 // The global object might be created from an object template with accessors.
3005 // Fill these accessors into the dictionary.
3006 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descs(map->instance_descriptors(isolate()),
3007 isolate());
3008 for (InternalIndex i : map->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
3009 PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
3010 // Only accessors are expected.
3011 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
3012 PropertyDetails d(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.attributes(),
3013 PropertyCellType::kMutable);
3014 DirectHandle<Name> name(descs->GetKey(i), isolate());
3015 DirectHandle<Object> value(descs->GetStrongValue(i), isolate());
3016 DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell = NewPropertyCell(name, d, value);
3017 // |dictionary| already contains enough space for all properties.
3018 USE(GlobalDictionary::Add(isolate(), dictionary, name, cell, d));
3019 }
3020
3021 // Allocate the global object and initialize it with the backing store.
3022 Handle<JSGlobalObject> global(
3023 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(New(map, AllocationType::kOld)), isolate());
3024 InitializeJSObjectFromMap(*global, *dictionary, *map,
3025 NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper);
3026
3027 // Create a new map for the global object.
3028 DirectHandle<Map> new_map = Map::CopyDropDescriptors(isolate(), map);
3029 Tagged<Map> raw_map = *new_map;
3030 raw_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
3031 raw_map->set_is_dictionary_map(true);
3032 LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(raw_map));
3033
3034 // Set up the global object as a normalized object.
3035 global->set_global_dictionary(*dictionary, kReleaseStore);
3036 global->set_map(isolate(), raw_map, kReleaseStore);
3037
3038 // Make sure result is a global object with properties in dictionary.
3039 DCHECK(IsJSGlobalObject(*global) && !global->HasFastProperties());
3040 return global;
3041}

3046 static_assert(JSSpecialObject::kCppHeapWrappableOffset ==
3047 JSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlots::kCppHeapWrappableOffset);

3052void Factory::InitializeJSObjectFromMap(Tagged<JSObject> obj,
3053 Tagged<Object> properties,
3054 Tagged<Map> map,
3055 NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
3056 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3057 obj->set_raw_properties_or_hash(properties, kRelaxedStore);
3058 obj->initialize_elements();
3059 // TODO(1240798): Initialize the object's body using valid initial values
3060 // according to the object's initial map. For example, if the map's
3061 // instance type is JS_ARRAY_TYPE, the length field should be initialized
3062 // to a number (e.g. Smi::zero()) and the elements initialized to a
3063 // fixed array (e.g. Heap::empty_fixed_array()). Currently, the object
3064 // verification code has to cope with (temporarily) invalid objects. See
3065 // for example, JSArray::JSArrayVerify).
3066 DCHECK_EQ(IsJSApiWrapperObject(map),
3067 new_js_object_type == NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper);
3068 InitializeJSObjectBody(obj, map,
3069 new_js_object_type == NewJSObjectType::kNoAPIWrapper
3070 ? JSObject::kHeaderSize
3071 : JSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlots::kHeaderSize);
3072 if (new_js_object_type == NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper) {
3073 InitializeCppHeapWrapper(obj);
3074 }
3075}
3076
3077void Factory::InitializeJSObjectBody(Tagged<JSObject> obj, Tagged<Map> map,
3078 int start_offset) {
3079 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3080 if (start_offset == map->instance_size()) return;
3081 DCHECK_LT(start_offset, map->instance_size());
3082
3083 // We cannot always fill with one_pointer_filler_map because objects
3084 // created from API functions expect their embedder fields to be initialized
3085 // with undefined_value.
3086 // Pre-allocated fields need to be initialized with undefined_value as well
3087 // so that object accesses before the constructor completes (e.g. in the
3088 // debugger) will not cause a crash.
3089
3090 // In case of Array subclassing the |map| could already be transitioned
3091 // to different elements kind from the initial map on which we track slack.
3092 bool in_progress = map->IsInobjectSlackTrackingInProgress();
3093 obj->InitializeBody(map, start_offset, in_progress,
3094 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate()).one_pointer_filler_map_word(),
3095 *undefined_value());
3096 if (in_progress) {
3097 map->FindRootMap(isolate())->InobjectSlackTrackingStep(isolate());
3098 }
3099}

3101Handle<JSObject> Factory::NewJSObjectFromMap(
3102 DirectHandle<Map> map, AllocationType allocation,
3103 DirectHandle<AllocationSite> allocation_site,
3104 NewJSObjectType new_js_object_type) {
3105 // JSFunctions should be allocated using AllocateFunction to be
3106 // properly initialized.
3107 DCHECK(!InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(*map));

3109 // Both types of global objects should be allocated using
3110 // AllocateGlobalObject to be properly initialized.
3111 DCHECK_NE(map->instance_type(), JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE);
3112

3114 AllocateRawWithAllocationSite(map, allocation, allocation_site));

3117 new_js_object_type);
3118
3119 DCHECK(js_obj->HasFastElements() ||
3120 (isolate()->bootstrapper()->IsActive() ||
3121 *map == isolate()
3122 ->raw_native_context()
3123 ->js_array_template_literal_object_map()) ||
3124 js_obj->HasTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElements() ||
3125 js_obj->HasFastStringWrapperElements() ||
3126 js_obj->HasFastArgumentsElements() ||
3127 js_obj->HasDictionaryElements() || js_obj->HasSharedArrayElements());
3128 return handle(js_obj, isolate());
3129}

3624 size_t element_size;

3692MaybeHandle<JSBoundFunction> Factory::NewJSBoundFunction(
3693 DirectHandle<JSReceiver> target_function, DirectHandle<JSAny> bound_this,
3694 base::Vector<DirectHandle<Object>> bound_args,
3695 DirectHandle<JSPrototype> prototype) {
3696 DCHECK(IsCallable(*target_function));
3697 static_assert(Code::kMaxArguments <= FixedArray::kMaxLength);
3698 if (bound_args.length() >= Code::kMaxArguments) {
3699 THROW_NEW_ERROR(isolate(),
3700 NewRangeError(MessageTemplate::kTooManyArguments));
3701 }
3702
3703 SaveAndSwitchContext save(isolate(),
3704 target_function->GetCreationContext().value());
3705
3706 // Create the [[BoundArguments]] for the result.
3707 DirectHandle<FixedArray> bound_arguments;
3708 if (bound_args.empty()) {
3709 bound_arguments = empty_fixed_array();
3710 } else {
3711 bound_arguments = NewFixedArray(bound_args.length());
3712 for (int i = 0; i < bound_args.length(); ++i) {
3713 bound_arguments->set(i, *bound_args[i]);
3714 }
3715 }
3716
3717 // Setup the map for the JSBoundFunction instance.
3718 DirectHandle<Map> map =
3719 IsConstructor(*target_function)
3720 ? isolate()->bound_function_with_constructor_map()
3721 : isolate()->bound_function_without_constructor_map();
3722 if (map->prototype() != *prototype) {
3723 map = Map::TransitionRootMapToPrototypeForNewObject(isolate(), map,
3724 prototype);
3725 }
3726 DCHECK_EQ(IsConstructor(*target_function), map->is_constructor());
3727
3728 // Setup the JSBoundFunction instance.
3729 Handle<JSBoundFunction> result =
3730 Cast<JSBoundFunction>(NewJSObjectFromMap(map, AllocationType::kYoung));
3731 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3732 Tagged<JSBoundFunction> raw = *result;
3733 raw->set_bound_target_function(Cast<JSCallable>(*target_function),
3734 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3735 raw->set_bound_this(*bound_this, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3736 raw->set_bound_arguments(*bound_arguments, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
3737 return result;
3738}

3778
3779void Factory::ReinitializeJSGlobalProxy(DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> object,
3780 DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor) {
3781 DCHECK(constructor->has_initial_map());
3782 DirectHandle<Map> map(constructor->initial_map(), isolate());
3783 DirectHandle<Map> old_map(object->map(), isolate());
3784
3785 // The proxy's hash should be retained across reinitialization.
3786 DirectHandle<Object> raw_properties_or_hash(object->raw_properties_or_hash(),
3787 isolate());
3788
3789 if (old_map->is_prototype_map()) {
3790 map = Map::Copy(isolate(), map, "CopyAsPrototypeForJSGlobalProxy");
3791 map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
3792 }
3793 JSObject::NotifyMapChange(old_map, map, isolate());
3794 old_map->NotifyLeafMapLayoutChange(isolate());
3795
3796 // Check that the already allocated object has the same size and type as
3797 // objects allocated using the constructor.
3798 DCHECK(map->instance_size() == old_map->instance_size());
3799 DCHECK(map->instance_type() == old_map->instance_type());
3800
3801 // In order to keep heap in consistent state there must be no allocations
3802 // before object re-initialization is finished.
3803 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3804
3805 // Reset the map for the object.
3806 Tagged<JSGlobalProxy> raw = *object;
3807 raw->set_map(isolate(), *map, kReleaseStore);
3808
3809 // Reinitialize the object from the constructor map.
3810 InitializeJSObjectFromMap(raw, *raw_properties_or_hash, *map,
3811 NewJSObjectType::kAPIWrapper);
3812 // Ensure that the object and constructor belongs to the same native context.
3813 DCHECK_EQ(object->map()->map(), constructor->map()->map());
3814}

3889int Factory::NumberToStringCacheHash(Tagged<Smi> number) {
3890 int mask = (number_string_cache()->length() >> 1) - 1;
3891 return number.value() & mask;
3892}
3893
3894int Factory::NumberToStringCacheHash(double number) {
3895 int mask = (number_string_cache()->length() >> 1) - 1;
3896 int64_t bits = base::bit_cast<int64_t>(number);
3897 return (static_cast<int>(bits) ^ static_cast<int>(bits >> 32)) & mask;
3898}
3899
3900Handle<String> Factory::SizeToString(size_t value, bool check_cache) {
3901 Handle<String> result;
3902 NumberCacheMode cache_mode =
3903 check_cache ? NumberCacheMode::kBoth : NumberCacheMode::kIgnore;
3904 if (value <= Smi::kMaxValue) {
3905 int32_t int32v = static_cast<int32_t>(static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
3906 // SmiToString sets the hash when needed, we can return immediately.
3907 return SmiToString(Smi::FromInt(int32v), cache_mode);
3908 } else if (value <= kMaxSafeInteger) {
3909 // TODO(jkummerow): Refactor the cache to not require Objects as keys.
3910 double double_value = static_cast<double>(value);
3911 result = HeapNumberToString(NewHeapNumber(double_value), value, cache_mode);
3912 } else {
3913 char arr[kNumberToStringBufferSize];
3914 base::Vector<char> buffer(arr, arraysize(arr));
3915 // Build the string backwards from the least significant digit.
3916 int i = buffer.length();
3917 size_t value_copy = value;
3918 buffer[--i] = '\0';
3919 do {
3920 buffer[--i] = '0' + (value_copy % 10);
3921 value_copy /= 10;
3922 } while (value_copy > 0);
3923 char* string = buffer.begin() + i;
3924 // No way to cache this; we'd need an {Object} to use as key.
3925 result = NewStringFromAsciiChecked(string);
3926 }
3927 {
3928 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
3929 Tagged<String> raw = *result;
3930 if (value <= JSArray::kMaxArrayIndex &&
3931 raw->raw_hash_field() == String::kEmptyHashField) {
3932 uint32_t raw_hash_field = StringHasher::MakeArrayIndexHash(
3933 static_cast<uint32_t>(value), raw->length());
3934 raw->set_raw_hash_field(raw_hash_field);
3935 }
3936 }
3937 return result;
3938}

4048Handle<Map> Factory::ObjectLiteralMapFromCache(
4049 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context, int number_of_properties) {
4050 // Use initial slow object proto map for too many properties.
4051 if (number_of_properties >= JSObject::kMapCacheSize) {
4052 return handle(context->slow_object_with_object_prototype_map(), isolate());
4053 }
4054 // TODO(chromium:1503456): remove once fixed.
4055 CHECK_LE(0, number_of_properties);
4056
4057 DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> cache(Cast<WeakFixedArray>(context->map_cache()),
4058 isolate());
4059
4060 // Check to see whether there is a matching element in the cache.
4061 Tagged<MaybeObject> result = cache->get(number_of_properties);
4062 Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object;
4063 if (result.GetHeapObjectIfWeak(&heap_object)) {
4064 Tagged<Map> map = Cast<Map>(heap_object);
4065 DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4066 return handle(map, isolate());
4067 }
4068
4069 // Create a new map and add it to the cache.
4070 Handle<Map> map = Map::Create(isolate(), number_of_properties);
4071 DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4072 cache->set(number_of_properties, MakeWeak(*map));
4073 return map;
4074}
