4261Handle<Map> Factory::CreateSloppyFunctionMap(
4262 FunctionMode function_mode,
4263 MaybeDirectHandle<JSFunction> maybe_empty_function) {
4264 bool has_prototype = IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode);
4265 int header_size = has_prototype ? JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype
4266 : JSFunction::kSizeWithoutPrototype;
4267 int descriptors_count = has_prototype ? 5 : 4;
4268 int inobject_properties_count = 0;
4269 if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) ++inobject_properties_count;
4270
4271 Handle<Map> map = NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4272 JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, header_size + inobject_properties_count * kTaggedSize,
4273 TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, inobject_properties_count);
4274 {
4275 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4276 Tagged<Map> raw_map = *map;
4277 raw_map->set_has_prototype_slot(has_prototype);
4278 raw_map->set_is_constructor(has_prototype);
4279 raw_map->set_is_callable(true);
4280 }
4281 DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function;
4282 if (maybe_empty_function.ToHandle(&empty_function)) {
4283 // Temporarily set constructor to empty function to calm down map verifier.
4284 map->SetConstructor(*empty_function);
4285 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, empty_function);
4286 } else {
4287 // |maybe_empty_function| is allowed to be empty only during empty function
4288 // creation.
4289 DCHECK(IsUndefined(
4290 isolate()->raw_native_context()->get(Context::EMPTY_FUNCTION_INDEX)));
4291 }
4292
4293 //
4294 // Setup descriptors array.
4295 //
4296 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, descriptors_count);
4297
4298 PropertyAttributes ro_attribs =
4299 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY);
4300 PropertyAttributes rw_attribs =
4301 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE);
4302 PropertyAttributes roc_attribs =
4303 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY);
4304
4305 int field_index = 0;
4306 static_assert(
4307 JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex == 0);
4308 { // Add length accessor.
4309 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4310 length_string(), function_length_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4311 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4312 }
4313
4314 static_assert(
4315 JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex == 1);
4316 if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) {
4317 // Add name field.
4318 DirectHandle<Name> name = isolate()->factory()->name_string();
4319 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), name, field_index++,
4320 roc_attribs, Representation::Tagged());
4321 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4322
4323 } else {
4324 // Add name accessor.
4325 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4326 name_string(), function_name_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4327 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4328 }
4329 { // Add arguments accessor.
4330 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4331 arguments_string(), function_arguments_accessor(), ro_attribs);
4332 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4333 }
4334 { // Add caller accessor.
4335 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4336 caller_string(), function_caller_accessor(), ro_attribs);
4337 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4338 }
4339 if (IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode)) {
4340 // Add prototype accessor.
4341 PropertyAttributes attribs =
4342 IsFunctionModeWithWritablePrototype(function_mode) ? rw_attribs
4343 : ro_attribs;
4344 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4345 prototype_string(), function_prototype_accessor(), attribs);
4346 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4347 }
4348 DCHECK_EQ(inobject_properties_count, field_index);
4349 DCHECK_EQ(
4350 0, map->instance_descriptors(isolate())->number_of_slack_descriptors());
4351 LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(*map));
4352 return map;
4353}

4355Handle<Map> Factory::CreateStrictFunctionMap(
4356 FunctionMode function_mode, DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function) {
4357 bool has_prototype = IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode);
4358 int header_size = has_prototype ? JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype
4359 : JSFunction::kSizeWithoutPrototype;
4360 int inobject_properties_count = 0;
4361 // length and prototype accessors or just length accessor.
4362 int descriptors_count = IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode) ? 2 : 1;
4363 if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) {
4364 ++inobject_properties_count; // name property.
4365 } else {
4366 ++descriptors_count; // name accessor.
4367 }
4368 descriptors_count += inobject_properties_count;
4369
4370 Handle<Map> map = NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4371 JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, header_size + inobject_properties_count * kTaggedSize,
4372 TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, inobject_properties_count);
4373 {
4374 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4375 Tagged<Map> raw_map = *map;
4376 raw_map->set_has_prototype_slot(has_prototype);
4377 raw_map->set_is_constructor(has_prototype);
4378 raw_map->set_is_callable(true);
4379 // Temporarily set constructor to empty function to calm down map verifier.
4380 raw_map->SetConstructor(*empty_function);
4381 }
4382 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, empty_function);
4383
4384 //
4385 // Setup descriptors array.
4386 //
4387 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, descriptors_count);
4388
4389 PropertyAttributes rw_attribs =
4390 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE);
4391 PropertyAttributes ro_attribs =
4392 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY);
4393 PropertyAttributes roc_attribs =
4394 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY);
4395
4396 int field_index = 0;
4397 static_assert(JSFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex == 0);
4398 { // Add length accessor.
4399 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4400 length_string(), function_length_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4401 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4402 }
4403
4404 static_assert(JSFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex == 1);
4405 if (IsFunctionModeWithName(function_mode)) {
4406 // Add name field.
4407 DirectHandle<Name> name = isolate()->factory()->name_string();
4408 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), name, field_index++,
4409 roc_attribs, Representation::Tagged());
4410 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4411
4412 } else {
4413 // Add name accessor.
4414 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4415 name_string(), function_name_accessor(), roc_attribs);
4416 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4417 }
4418
4419 if (IsFunctionModeWithPrototype(function_mode)) {
4420 // Add prototype accessor.
4421 PropertyAttributes attribs =
4422 IsFunctionModeWithWritablePrototype(function_mode) ? rw_attribs
4423 : ro_attribs;
4424 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
4425 prototype_string(), function_prototype_accessor(), attribs);
4426 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
4427 }
4428 DCHECK_EQ(inobject_properties_count, field_index);
4429 DCHECK_EQ(
4430 0, map->instance_descriptors(isolate())->number_of_slack_descriptors());
4431 LOG(isolate(), MapDetails(*map));
4432 return map;
4433}

4520Handle<JSSharedStruct> Factory::NewJSSharedStruct(
4521 DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor,
4522 MaybeDirectHandle<NumberDictionary> maybe_elements_template) {
4523 SharedObjectSafePublishGuard publish_guard;
4524
4525 DirectHandle<Map> instance_map(constructor->initial_map(), isolate());
4526 DirectHandle<PropertyArray> property_array;
4527 const int num_oob_fields =
4528 instance_map->NumberOfFields(ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous) -
4529 instance_map->GetInObjectProperties();
4530 if (num_oob_fields > 0) {
4531 property_array =
4532 NewPropertyArray(num_oob_fields, AllocationType::kSharedOld);
4533 }
4534
4535 DirectHandle<NumberDictionary> elements_dictionary;
4536 bool has_elements_dictionary;
4537 if ((has_elements_dictionary =
4538 maybe_elements_template.ToHandle(&elements_dictionary))) {
4539 elements_dictionary = NumberDictionary::ShallowCopy(
4540 isolate(), elements_dictionary, AllocationType::kSharedOld);
4541 }
4542
4543 Handle<JSSharedStruct> instance = Cast<JSSharedStruct>(
4544 NewJSObject(constructor, AllocationType::kSharedOld));
4545
4546 // The struct object has not been fully initialized yet. Disallow allocation
4547 // from this point on.
4548 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4549 if (!property_array.is_null()) instance->SetProperties(*property_array);
4550 if (has_elements_dictionary) instance->set_elements(*elements_dictionary);
4551
4552 return instance;
4553}

4687Factory::JSFunctionBuilder::JSFunctionBuilder(
4688 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi,
4689 DirectHandle<Context> context)
4690 : isolate_(isolate), sfi_(sfi), context_(context) {}
4691
4692Handle<JSFunction> Factory::JSFunctionBuilder::Build() {
4693 DirectHandle<Code> code(sfi_->GetCode(isolate_), isolate_);
4694 // Retain the code across the call to BuildRaw, because it allocates and can
4695 // trigger code to be flushed. Otherwise the SFI's compiled state and the
4696 // function's compiled state can diverge, and the call to PostInstantiation
4697 // below can fail to initialize the feedback vector.
4698 IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(sfi_->is_compiled_scope(isolate_));
4699 Handle<JSFunction> result = BuildRaw(code);
4700
4701 if (code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE) {
4702 JSFunction::EnsureFeedbackVector(isolate_, result, &is_compiled_scope);
4703 }
4704
4705 Compiler::PostInstantiation(isolate_, result, &is_compiled_scope);
4706 return result;
4707}
4708
4709Handle<JSFunction> Factory::JSFunctionBuilder::BuildRaw(
4710 DirectHandle<Code> code) {
4711 Isolate* isolate = isolate_;
4712 Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
4713
4714 DirectHandle<Map> map;
4715 if (!maybe_map_.ToHandle(&map)) {
4716 // No specific map requested, use the default.
4717 map = direct_handle(
4718 Cast<Map>(context_->native_context()->get(sfi_->function_map_index())),
4719 isolate_);
4720 }
4721 DCHECK(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(*map));
4722
4723 // Allocation.
4724 Tagged<JSFunction> function =
4725 Cast<JSFunction>(factory->New(map, allocation_type_));
4726 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
4727
4728 // Transition the feedback cell after allocating the JSFunction. This is so
4729 // that the leap-tiering-relevant one-to-many feedback cell mutation below
4730 // happens atomically with the closure count increase here, without the object
4731 // verifier potentially observing a many-closures cell with context
4732 // specialised code.
4733 DirectHandle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell;
4734 FeedbackCell::ClosureCountTransition cell_transition;
4735 if (maybe_feedback_cell_.ToHandle(&feedback_cell)) {
4736 // Track the newly-created closure.
4737 cell_transition = feedback_cell->IncrementClosureCount(isolate_);
4738 } else {
4739 // Fall back to the many_closures_cell.
4740 feedback_cell = isolate_->factory()->many_closures_cell();
4741 cell_transition = FeedbackCell::kMany;
4742 }
4743
4744 WriteBarrierMode mode = allocation_type_ == AllocationType::kYoung
4745 ? SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER
4746 : UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
4747 // Header initialization.
4748 function->initialize_properties(isolate);
4749 function->initialize_elements();
4750 function->set_shared(*sfi_, mode);
4751 function->set_context(*context_, kReleaseStore, mode);
4752 function->set_raw_feedback_cell(*feedback_cell, mode);
4753#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4754 // If the FeedbackCell doesn't have a dispatch handle, we need to allocate a
4755 // dispatch entry now. This should only be the case for functions using the
4756 // generic many_closures_cell (for example builtin functions), and only for
4757 // functions using certain kinds of code.
4758 if (feedback_cell->dispatch_handle() == kNullJSDispatchHandle) {
4759 DCHECK_EQ(*feedback_cell, *factory->many_closures_cell());
4760 // We currently only expect to see these kinds of Code here. For BASELINE
4761 // code, we will allocate a FeedbackCell after building the JSFunction. See
4762 // JSFunctionBuilder::Build.
4763 DCHECK(code->kind() == CodeKind::BUILTIN ||
4764 code->kind() == CodeKind::JS_TO_WASM_FUNCTION ||
4765 code->kind() == CodeKind::BASELINE);
4766 // TODO(saelo): in the future, we probably want to use
4767 // code->parameter_count() here instead, but not all Code objects know
4768 // their parameter count yet.
4769 function->AllocateDispatchHandle(
4770 isolate, sfi_->internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver(), *code,
4771 mode);
4772 } else {
4773 // TODO(olivf, 42204201): Here we are explicitly not updating (only
4774 // potentially initializing) the code. Worst case the dispatch handle still
4775 // contains bytecode or CompileLazy and we'll tier on the next call. Otoh,
4776 // if we would UpdateCode we would risk tiering down already existing
4777 // closures with optimized code installed.
4778 JSDispatchHandle handle = feedback_cell->dispatch_handle();
4779 JSDispatchTable* jdt = IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table();
4780 Tagged<Code> old_code = jdt->GetCode(handle);
4781
4782 // A write barrier is needed when settings code, because the update can race
4783 // with marking which could leave the dispatch slot unmarked.
4784 // TODO(olivf): This should be fixed by using a more traditional WB
4785 // for dispatch handles (i.e. have a marking queue with dispatch handles
4786 // instead of marking through the handle).
4787 constexpr WriteBarrierMode mode_if_setting_code =
4788 WriteBarrierMode::UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER;
4789
4790 // TODO(olivf): We should go through the cases where this is still
4791 // needed and maybe find some alternative to initialize it correctly
4792 // from the beginning.
4793 if (old_code->is_builtin()) {
4794 jdt->SetCodeNoWriteBarrier(handle, *code);
4795 function->set_dispatch_handle(handle, mode_if_setting_code);
4796 } else {
4797 // On a transition of a feedback cell from one closure to many, make sure
4798 // that the code on the feedback cell isn't native context specialized,
4799 // and if it was, eagerly re-optimize.
4800 if (cell_transition == FeedbackCell::kOneToMany &&
4801 old_code->is_context_specialized()) {
4802 jdt->SetCodeNoWriteBarrier(handle, *code);
4803 function->set_dispatch_handle(handle, mode_if_setting_code);
4804 DCHECK(old_code->kind() == CodeKind::MAGLEV ||
4805 old_code->kind() == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS);
4806 if (!old_code->marked_for_deoptimization()) {
4807 function->RequestOptimization(isolate, old_code->kind());
4808 }
4809 } else {
4810 function->set_dispatch_handle(handle, mode);
4811 }
4812 }
4813 }
4814#else
4815 USE(cell_transition);
4816 function->UpdateCode(*code, mode);
4817#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4818 if (function->has_prototype_slot()) {
4819 function->set_prototype_or_initial_map(
4820 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).the_hole_value(), kReleaseStore,
4821 SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
4822 }
4823
4824 // Potentially body initialization.
4825 factory->InitializeJSObjectBody(
4826 function, *map, JSFunction::GetHeaderSize(map->has_prototype_slot()));
4827
4828 return handle(function, isolate_);
4829}
